  ["_base_energy_2"] = {
    identifier = "_base_energy_2",
    category_id = "_base_general",
    sidebar_text = "High Voltage Energy",
    page_type = "Global",
    paragraphs = {
      {
        paragraphType = "Header",
        header = "High-Voltage-Power",
        text = "",
        image = nil,
        overrideMaxHeight = false,
        customMaxHeightPx = 0,
        addImageText = false,
        imageTextData = {},
      },
      {
        paragraphType = "Text",
        header = "",
        text = [[In FOUNDRY there are two different types of power, low and high voltage, this page is about high voltage power.

Advanced energy-generation machinery generates high-voltage-power (HVP), which is transported by power poles and power lines. To convert HVP to low-voltage-power (LVP), which is distributed through building blocks, a transformer needs to be placed on the according building block foundation and connected to the HVP via a power line.

<u><b>Important:</b> Even if high-voltage power-generating machines require a foundation, they only output their generated power to a connected HVP-grid.</u>

<b>Transformers</b> have a maximum transmission rate, sometimes multiple transformers might be necessary, depending on the amount of power consuming machinery on the low-voltage grid.

<b>Power lines</b> can be crafted, after you equip them you can click on a connect-able object to start a power line, and click again on the desired end point (e.g. solar panel to power pole, or pole to pole).]],
